16 2021-01-24 injection site pain Client came to be vaccinated accompanied by her father on Saturday January 23, 2021. The greeting ta... Read more
Close
Client came to be vaccinated accompanied by her father on Saturday January 23, 2021. The greeting table in the front was very busy and a lot going on. The client had registered online and had her paper to prove it when she was escorted to he next tables to be registered. There was nothing adverse about her registration form. Date of birth was listed, however, it was not caught that she was less than 18 to receive Moderna. We advertise that it is the Moderna vaccine that we have. Father never said anything and stood off to the side waiting for her to be observed for 15 minutes. On Monday, January 25, I spoke with client who answered phone, to explain what happened and to see if she was OK. States her arm at injection site hurt a little, but nothing else. I said I would call each day to make sure she was OK. Later in the day, she left a message to call her. I called and she wanted to know what vaccine she would get as her second dose. I said it would not be Moderna and that I could find some information and call her back. Then she states she has a lawyer and to whom should she address it to. I said the Health Officer at the city.
16 2021-02-03 vaccination site pain 16 year old inadvertently received the vaccine; sore arm; supposed to receive the Pfizer vaccine but... Read more
Close
16 year old inadvertently received the vaccine; sore arm; supposed to receive the Pfizer vaccine but received the Moderna covid-19 vaccine by mistake; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional (HCP) concerning a 16-year-old, female consumer who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) was less than 18 years old and had a sore arm. The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 06 Jan 2021 prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number : 025J20A) intramuscularly in the left deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 06 Jan 2021, a 16-year-old patient was inadvertently vaccinated. The patient was supposed to receive Pfizer vaccine but received Moderna COVID- 19 vaccine by mistake. The patient experienced a sore arm but no other known symptoms. No treatment was received for the sore arm. Action taken with the second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported. The event, vaccine given to a patient less than 18-years-old, and wrong drug administered was considered resolved. The outcome for the patient's sore arm was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 16-year-old female patient who received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot unknown), reporting Product administered to patient of inappropriate age and Wrong product administered with an associated non-serious expected event of Injection site pain. No treatment received for the event. Based on temporal association between the use of the product and the onset of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Had very mild pain in left arm; 16 year old daughter injected with Moderna vaccine; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer, concerning a 16-year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine, where 16-year-old daughter injected with Moderna vaccine had very mild pain in left arm. The patient's medical history reported included severe asthma. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 28 JAN 2021, prior to the onset of event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number unknown) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 28 JAN 2021, a 16-year-old patient was injected with vaccine and had no reactions of fever or any other adverse events. Later, on an unspecified date in 2021, she also experienced very mild pain in her left arm where she was vaccinated. The patient was under asthma medications twice a day for her asthma. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events were not reported. The outcome of the event, 16-year-old daughter injected with Moderna vaccine was considered resolved on 28 JAN 2021. The outcome of the event had very mild pain in left arm was considered unknown at the time of this report.; Reporter's Comments: The events developed on same day after first dose of mRNA-1372. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event of vaccination site pain, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Injection site pain and tenderness; 16 year old patient administered the vaccine; A spontaneous report was received from a health care provider regarding a 16-year-old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) inappropriately at the age of 16 and experienced injection site pain and tenderness/vaccination site pain. The patient's medical history was not included. Products known to have been used by the patient were Vitamin D3 and ethinylestradiol, ferrous fumarate, norethisterone. On 12 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient inappropriately received the first of two doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 031M20A) intramuscularly in the right deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 13 Feb 2021, the day after the vaccine was given the patient experienced injection site pain and tenderness. Treatment information was not provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 was not reported. The outcome of the events, vaccine being given inappropriately to a 16-year-old, was considered resolved on 12 Feb 2021. The event, vaccine site pain and tenderness, was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 16-year-old female patient who received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot 031M20A), reporting Product administered to patient of inappropriate age with associated adverse event of vaccination site pain. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the onset date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Close
Patient was screened and identified allergy to PCN. Covid Vaccine administered without incident. Nurse did insist client stay in area for 30 minutes due to history of PCN allergy. After about 10 minutes, client returned with complaint of itching, flushing in face and hyperventilating. LPH assisted and laid patient down and elevated her legs. Pulse was 200 and breathing difficulties increased. EPI 0.5 given IM in thigh by nurse. Patient felt significantly better after one dose of EPI and breathing was almost back to normal. Patient transported by EMS.

Close
Rash and itchiness started at around 10 PM on 1/7/2021. Rash described as "traveling across chest" and similar to what happens when she takes prednisone. Stated she has not taken prednisone for over a year. Client stated that rash did not appear anywhere else on her body. Itchiness was experienced on chest and arms only. Client also stated symptoms of fatigue, muscle weakness, and "super sore arm" that lasted from day of vaccination until 1/10/2021. Client also reported a headache that lasted 2 day after vaccination. She contacted her provider on 1/7/2021 and, per provider's instruction, took 1 tablet of Benadryl. Client was unsure of dosage of Benadryl. On the morning of 1/8/2021 she took a second tablet of Benadryl and reported that her rash resolved after the second dose of Benadryl. Her itchiness resolved the morning of 1/9/2021. Stated that her Doctor did not specify a diagnosis but did state to hold off on the second dose of this vaccine.

18 2021-01-14 hives I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or ... Read more
Close
I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or an hour after. About 2 hours later (at 2:00 pm), I developed some hives around my neck, and the part of my arm near the injection site started to become more and more sore. I applied Benadryl to the hives and they went away. However, my left arm hurt to touch or move, much worse than any vaccine I've had before (flu, HPV). That night, I had trouble sleeping because the discomfort because of the sore left arm. I also could not sleep because of chest tightness and pressure, which worsened when lying down, but that pressure did not progress to the point of wheezing (I have asthma). Sleeping on my back was the only option because sleeping on either side was painful, which worsened the chest pressure. When I woke up, my fingers felt stiff and I had joint pain in both hands, more so in my left hand. Throughout this, I did not see any redness on my arm. This day it was agonizing to move my left arm. I could pick things up, but raising it above my the height of my waist or twisting it behind my back to get on my backpack was near impossible and was avoided. The chest pressure went away. The second night, I still had trouble sleeping, but the pain was much better, although I still could not sleep on my side. When I woke up, I had no more joint pain. That day, although the left arm was still sore, I could move it pretty well. If I made too strong of a movement, it felt like the injection site would tense up, the pain would slowly ramp up, and then diminish. That afternoon, at 4:30, I was able to play tennis with minimal soreness, and that night, I was able to sleep on my side. The following day, I had a cough, but that might have been because I didn't dress for the weather, and experiences close to zero soreness.

Close
1/24/21 morning, 10 days after getting 1st dose of vaccination, broke out in hives in several places on both feet. The next day more hives appeared on knees and the ones on feet got worse. The day after that hives also appeared on hips and elbows. On 1/27 went to Doctor's office and received steroid shot to stop the allergic reaction. Took 5-7 days for all the hives to disappear. Based on the allergic reaction to the first dose, doctor recommended not taking the second dose as reaction could be more severe and/or have an asthma attack.
18 2021-02-03 injection site pain For my first dose, I had quite mild symptoms. I woke up with a migraine the next morning and some so... Read more
Close
For my first dose, I had quite mild symptoms. I woke up with a migraine the next morning and some soreness at the injection site. Both of these lasted a couple of days and were able to be treated with over-the-counter pain medicine. My second dose, however, provided much worse flu-like symptoms. About 12 hours after I received the injection, I was woken with a migraine much worse than the first, nausea, chills, joint pain, sore throat, and fatigue. While the chills and nausea subsided, the other symptoms persisted until the next day. As of today (2/4/21), all symptoms are gone except for soreness at the injection site.

18 2021-03-10 rash 18 year old female came to hospital for chest tightness, choking sensation in the throat as well as ... Read more
Close
18 year old female came to hospital for chest tightness, choking sensation in the throat as well as skin rash after receiving COVID-19 vaccine. Initially patient presented to emergency room but subsequently discharged on steroid and Benadryl. Patient had continued episode of choking as well as chest tightness and skin rash for that patient came back to emergency room. Patient had received total 5 doses of epi pen because of that. Patient was admitted to medical floor initially. Patient was given steroid, Benadryl and famotidine. Patient had 2 episodes on medical floor where she started feeling choking and chest tightness. Patient remained stable hemodynamically except for tachycardia. Patient was transferred to intensive care unit for close monitoring. D-dimer was negative, urine tox screen was negative, COVID-19 PCR was negative, EKG showed sinus tachycardia. CT scan of neck was negative. We had discussed that patient has remained stable hemodynamically in the intensive care unit and discharge planning was discussed and patient was getting ready to be discharged when she had another episode where after drinking soda patient started having that choking sensation, patient remained stable hemodynamically during this episode as well. Her symptoms had improved. She looked visibly anxious. Patient was monitored in the ICU for few more hours and patient remained stable. I checked back on her and she was able to eat her lunch. She probably had a allergic reaction to more than a vaccine but subsequent episodes are thought to be secondary to anxiety attack given situation.

Approximately 15-20 minutes after vaccination patient developed weakness in her limbs. BP and glucose were normal. Approximately 10 minutes after the onset of symptoms the patient developed bright red rash on the face, increased breath rate, and swelling of the lips and tongue. She was having difficulty talking due to shortness of breath and swelling in the tongue. 911 was called and epinephrine 0.3mg IM was administered as well as diphenhydramine 100mg orally. Her rash improved fairly quickly, swelling went down a small amount. She stated breathing still felt labored and she was feeling like her heart was racing but she was also tired (likely due to medications administered). She was still having difficulty talking, taking short breaths between almost each word. Paramedics arrived approximately 12 minutes after epinephrine was administered. They attempted to walk her to the ambulance per her request, however she was unable to feel her legs. She was placed on a stretcher and into the ambulance. The patient stated she was given additional epinephrine in the ambulance as her condition had worsened by the time they got her in there. She was taken to the ER and given additional diphenhydramine and was observed until approximately midnight, when she said she was discharged. Follow up was completed the following day, and she had improved dramatically. She was still feeling a bit weak, but no longer had any issues breathing.

Red round rump below the deltoid muscle; Red round rump below the deltoid muscle; Injection was wrongly administered at the wrong muscle site; A spontaneous report was received from a nurse, concerning a 19-year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and developed red round lump below the deltoid muscle/ vaccination site mass and vaccination site erythema, injection was wrongly administered at the wrong muscle site/ incorrect route of product administration. The patient's medical history was not reported. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 06 Jan 2021, prior to onset of event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 025L20A) on right arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On an unknown date, after vaccination, the patient developed red round lump below the deltoid muscle and the patient's mother believed that the injection was wrongly administered at the wrong muscle site. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was unknown. The outcome of the event red round lump below the deltoid muscle was unknown. The outcome of event injection was wrongly administered at the wrong muscle site was considered resolved on 06 Jan 2021.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a case of Product administration error for mRNA-1273, lot # 025L20A with associated AEs. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Close
On the night I received the COVID-19 vaccine, I had a fever that went up to 103 degrees Fahrenheit. In the morning 24 hours after I had the second dose of the COVID-19 vaccine, I felt a little better from the night's fever and ate instant ramen, oranges, acetaminophen, and a vitamin C tablet. This was at about 8:45 AM. A few minutes or a minute after I swallowed the acetaminophen and vitamin C, I got a severe allergic reaction that led to me going to the Emergency Room. I have eaten these things before and am not allergic to acetaminophen, vitamin C, or anything in the instant ramen. The reaction was first felt by a shortness of breath and I could barely breath. Then, hives started to form on my face and my lips and face became extremely swollen. I then ended up throwing up after my mom gave be a Benadryl pill and I drank another Benadryl after. My face had become less swollen but it was still difficult to breath and hives started to form all over my body so we decided to rush to the Emergency Room. We got to the Emergency Room at about 9:30 AM and the hives on my body were worse. They were able to calm down the reaction by giving me more Benadryl through an IV and steroids. They knew I had the second dose of the vaccine so they did not give me anything that would suppress my immune system. Timewise, it could be the acetaminophen, but I have taken acetaminophen in the past many times before without a reaction.

Lupus; Obstruction breathing; Lips were swollen; Hives on face/ huge welts all over body; Fever; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 20-year-old, adult female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced lupus/systemic lupus erythematosus, fever/pyrexia, hives on face/huge welts all over body/urticaria, lips were swollen/lip swelling and obstruction breathing/obstructive airways disorder. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On an unspecified date in Jan 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: Unknown) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On an unspecified date in Feb 2021, Patient received the second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: Unknown) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On an unspecified date in Feb 2021, within 24 hours after receiving the second dose, patient experienced fever, hives on face/huge welts all over body, lips were swollen and obstruction breathing. The patient went to the ER and was given unspecified steriods and Diphenhydramine and the patient went to the ER (emergency room) on 19 Mar 2021 because she had another reaction and the doctor confirmed her that the vaccine triggered lupus. The event lupus was considered as medically significant. The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the events; therefore, action taken with the drug in response to the events was not applicable. The outcome of the events, lupus, fever, hives on face/huge welts all over body, lips were swollen and obstruction breathing was unknown at the time of this report.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

21 2021-02-04 injection site inflammation, injection site redness, injection site warmth, injection site pain, injection site pruritus, injection site swelling About 3-4 hours after the injection was given, my left arm began to hurt at the sight of the injecti... Read more
Close
About 3-4 hours after the injection was given, my left arm began to hurt at the sight of the injection. It was sore red and beginning to swell. After a couple more hours it was difficult to even move my arm; it felt as if my tricep was almost entirely immobilized. These symptoms persisted for about three days, with increasingly less intensity, and after the fourth day, I had no adverse symptoms. Exactly six days after receiving the vaccine, the area where the injection was given (tricep) began to feel itchy. When I tried to scratch it, the itch was not relieved but only worsened and began to swell and turn red. By the following day (7 days after injection), the site of injection and area surrounding the site of injection (about 6 inches along my upper and 3-4 inches in width) had swelled up more and was significantly more inflamed than my opposite arm which hadn't changed at all. It had a similar swelling, itch, and pain to the sensation one experiences after getting bitten by a mosquito, but in this case a very very large mosquito bite. By the evening of the seventh day, I began feeling very fatigued both mentally and physically and felt very subtle body aches that usually signal the early signs of a fever (at least for me). Upon feeling feverish symptoms I made a drink of turmeric and ginger root powder with honey and laid down for about an hour in an attempt to rest. After an hour, the body aches and fatigue lessened in intensity but my arm was still swelling and now feeling hot in temperature. The itching was unbearable. I went to go take a warm shower later that night and started to feel a mixture of pressure and pain traveling up my arm and into my chest. I began feeling my lymph nodes on the left side of my breast to find that a lymph node in my armpit and another one on the side of my breast had enlarged to about two inches in diameter. They were painful to the touch and noticeably sore when left untouched. These symptoms persisted with no change for about 2 days. After two days, the swelling and itching in my arm went away but my lymph nodes were still inflamed. They did not reduce in size or in pain until about 7 days after the first signs of these symptoms. After a week all symptoms went away.

He stepped away and shortly afterwards patient started complaining that her throat felt strange and was making it hard to breathe. The doctor immediately came back over, found patient was having difficulty breathing and holding herself upright in the chair. I held her by the shoulders to keep her from falling while the doctor also steadied her and asked a worker in the room for an epi-pen. The worker didn't seem to react much to the request so he told her louder that he needed an epi-pen. She started searching her area and the doctor started yelling across the room to others that he needed an epi-pen. It seemed like others initially took the demand less urgently than they should, but eventually someone came with an epi-pen. By this time I don't think patient was very conscious, if at all. Sometime during this time the doctor also instructed someone to call 911. The doctor tried using the epi-pen but at first he had some kind of cap on it that prevented it from working. He removed the cap and not finding an easy way to have a sterilized injection site he injected the epi-pen through patient's jeans. Soon afterwards a cot was brought out and workers had me step aside as they took patient and put her on the cot. Patient seemed to gradually become more aware of her surroundings and it wasn't long before she appeared to me to be fully conscious once again. They checked her blood pressure and pulse and maybe did other tests during this time. Eventually the ambulance arrived and patient was very clear with everyone that she did not want to incur the expenses of riding in the ambulance and I offered to bring her wherever they suggested that she should go. They watched and evaluated her for a while and eventually had her sign the form declining the ambulance transportation. They suggested that she make an appointment with her doctor but did not suggest that we take patient to an emergency room. We departed and patient did not afterward seem to experience any symptoms from the vaccine other than some of the general feelings of being sick, soreness at the injection site, etc. that others report with the Moderna vaccine.

I received an allergy immunotherapy shot the day before my first dose of the vaccine and instantly felt nauseous and extremely tired after receiving the vaccine, which continued for two days after receiving tut. Three days later, I woke up struggling to breathe (but not anaphylactic), covered in hives, itchy all over, shaking, disoriented, and chilled but not truly feverish. I reported this to my allergist, who prescribed prednisone and suggested the vaccine combined with immunotherapy were too much for my immune system for one week. The hives, itchiness, and difficulty breathing lasted about four days. I struggled with fatigue and nausea for over two weeks, stopping all school and work in the meantime. After my second dose, I feel just a bit tired and sore, so I think this truly was a bad reaction to the two injections combined rather than to the vaccine itself. Still, it was a debilitating experience, and I would recommend considering putting out guidance that other immunotherapy patients space out their allergy injections and vaccines farther than I did.

Patient reported: fast heartbeat, bad rash all over body, dizziness / weakness, shaking, full body tremor, severe itching - within 4 hours of receiving vaccination - went to Emergency Department. This is a pleasant 22-year-old female with past medical history of anxiety and depression who presents for possible allergic reaction. Patient states that at 12:08 p.m. just prior to arrival she received the 2nd COVID-19 vaccine. She states that immediately following the administration of this she became hot, flushed and sweaty. She then began having itching and hives. She denies any difficulty breathing. She denies any swelling of the lips or tongue. No difficulty swallowing. No shortness of breath or chest pain. No recent illness. No nausea or vomiting. Patient is a nonsmoker and denies alcohol or drug use. She denies pregnancy with a history of IUD.Clinical presentation concerning for allergic reaction. This is a 22-year-old female who developed itching, rash and throat tightness following her 2nd COVID-19 vaccine. Patient is hemodynamically stable. She is anxious in appearance. No obvious edema of the lips or tongue. No respiratory distress. No stridor. She is 98% on room air. In IVs immediately established. She is given 125 mg of Solu-Medrol, 20 Pepcid and 50 of Benadryl. Following all of her medications, she no longer has any of her symptoms. Her rash and hives has completely resolved. I discussed this with Dr. who was in agreement that she is stable for discharge. She will be sent home on additional 3 day course of prednisone to be started tomorrow, clear 10 for 10 days and Pepcid for 10 days. Questions addressed and answered prior to discharge. Patient discharged home in stable condition.

22 2021-02-16 injection site pruritus, injection site numbness, injection site pain Aggravated very quickly; Everything went blank; She can't talk and when she tries to talk she feels ... Read more
Close
Aggravated very quickly; Everything went blank; She can't talk and when she tries to talk she feels like she has the hiccups where she can barely get the words to talk; when she has a hiccup her whole chest hurts; Hiccup; Numbness; Her whole right side would jerk uncontrollably; Weak; fever; itching; sore arm / burning; chills; A spontaneous report (United States) was received from a consumer who was also a 22-year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine who experienced sore arm/ burning (injection site pain), fever (pyrexia), chills, itching (injection site pruritus), numbness (injection site numbness), weak (asthenia), whole right side would jerk uncontrollably (myoclonus), everything went blank (loss of consciousness), couldn't talk and when she tried to talk she felt like she had the hiccups (aphasia), her whole chest hurt (chest discomfort), and quickly became aggravated (anger). The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 06 Jan 2021, the patient received her first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in her right deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 06 Jan 2021, the patient experienced a sore arm, fever, chills, itching and burning. On 07 Jan 2021, on the site where the patient received the injection, she felt numbness and weak. Her whole right-side body would jerk uncontrollably. The patient went to two emergency rooms where they stated they did not know what was wrong and gave her a steroid injection that temporarily helped calm her down. On 08 Jan 2021, the patient stared at the door and everything went blank. She could not talk and when she tried to talk, she felt like she had the hiccups. She experienced her whole chest hurting when she had a hiccup. On 25 Jan 2021 and 26 Jan 2021, the patient saw two neurologists, who did testing. The patient's jerking was random, there were no triggers for it, and she did not know how to control or stop it. These adverse reactions made the patient become aggravated very quickly, which was not like her. On an unknown date, the patient stated it was the first day in the past month she had been able to talk all day. Treatment for the events included a steroid shot. Action taken with the second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported. The outcome for the events, sore arm/ burning, fever, chills, itching, numbness, weak, whole right side would jerk uncontrollably, everything went blank, couldn't talk and when she tried to talk she felt like she had the hiccups and her whole chest hurt, and quickly became aggravated, was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information which indicates a strong temporal association between the use of the product and the onset of the reported events a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Chills, fever, injection site pruritus and injection site pain are consistent with the known safety profile of mRNA-1273.

Patient received first dose of Moderna Covid19 vaccine at 0812. She was advised to stay in the observation area for 15 min. At the 15 min mark 0827, the patient reported to feeling funny. She expressed tightness on her forehead and numbing of her throat. After 5-10 minutes, she expressed her surrounding face (outer cheeks, forehead) started to feel tingling. Her Watch read her heart rate to be 153 BPM. She was closely monitored for 45 min after onset of symptoms. She was sipping water and was given a single dose of diphenhydramine 25mg at 0845 once noted that symptoms were not worsening. She remained upright, and alert. No SOB, wheezing, lip/tongue swelling were noted. Symptoms started to subside around 0900, HR was 120 BPM, numbness in throat was going away. We contacted her emergency contact at 0910 for continuous monitoring. Sent patient home with two extra doses of diphenhydramine 25mg to be given 4 hours later if symptoms still present, and advised the patients aunt to monitor for 4 hours for worsening of symptoms.

I received the dose at 1:45 pm on 1/13/2021 at Medical Center. Almost 1 hour post vaccine I started to feel a lump in my throat, as the minutes passed my throat started to feel tighter and fight and flight mode kicked in. It was hard to swallow, my tongue was swelling and I called EMS at 2:40 pm 1/13/2021. EMS noticed hives on my chest and left arm where I got the first dose of Moderna. I received epinephrine IM and IV benadryl in the ambulance. I was sinus tachycardic with heart rate in the 140s oxygen was 99% room air, lungs clear.. I was taken to ER where I was on observation for 2 hours. I was discharged around 5:10 pm on 1/13/2021. On my car ride home around 5:40pm I again started to feel my throat tighten, tongue swell, and heart race. I called EMS again, and was treated with IV benadryl, and epinephrine IM. I was taken to Medical Center where I was given IV solu-medrol and got blood taken and a pregnancy test done. My potassium was 3.1 and I took 2 potassium tablets to supplement. My EKG was normal sinus tach, oxygen 100% room air, blood pressure 140s/90s and got down to 120/80s. I was transported to another Medical Center for overnight observation because first Medical Center was full.

I received my second dose of the Moderna COVID vaccine at approx. 10:40 AM on Friday, January 29 at clinic. By 12:00 PM, I noticed that I developed facial swelling, which was most significant around my eyes, and I felt lethargic. Between 12:00 PM and 2:00 PM, I developed hives on my neck, chest, stomach, and arms, which prompted me to take 1/2 of a dose of 25mg Benadryl. Nonetheless, the symptoms persisted and I began to experience dizziness and tightness in my throat around 4-5 PM, which was when I was advised by a nurse to go to the emergency room for treatment. I arrived at Hospital's Emergency Department around 6:00 PM and I was treated for "Possible Allergic Reaction Major." I received diphenhydrAMINE (BENADRYL) injection 50 mg, famotidine (PF) (PEPCID) injection 20 mg, methylPREDNISolone sodium succinate (PF) (SOLU-MEDROL) injection 125 mg, sodium chloride 0.9 % iv bolus, and acetaminophen (TYLENOL) tablet 650 mg. I was discharged after 10:00 PM and sent home with a prescription for predniSONE 20 mg and famotidine 20 mg. My facial swelling and hives have gone down but neither have completely resolved since being discharged. I am also experiencing full body aches and fatigue at this time (3 PM on Saturday, January 30).

On the morning of 1/8/2021 (exactly 6 days after the first dose of the Moderna vaccine), I woke up with large hives concentrated mostly on my upper body (face, neck, chest, stomach). I tried taking various antihistamines (excluding Benadryl, which would later prove effective) to combat the hives, but they were largely ineffective. The hives shifted throughout the day, starting in my upper body and working their way down to my lower extremities. The next day, exactly one week after receiving the vaccine, I woke up with worse hives (now all over my body, mostly concentrated on my stomach, hips, and legs) and angioedema in my face. At this point, I went to the hospital and received a course of IV fluids/steroids/Benadryl/anti-nausea medication and all symptoms subsisted. Symptoms returned a few hours after discharge, where I continued an oral regimen of the aforementioned medications. The next day, 8 days after the initial dose, my symptoms were equally severe and coupled with gastrointestinal distress, feverishness (likely due to dehydration from the Benadryl) and nausea. This morning (1/11/2021), 9 days after receiving the vaccine, my hives have largely subsisted. In summation, starting 6 days after receiving my first dose of the Moderna vaccine, I experienced 3 full days and nights of severe hives and swelling.

Passed out twice; Pain in the injection site; Slight headache; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 24-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced the events, passed out twice, pain in the injection site, and slight headache. The patient's medical history was not reported. No concomitant medications were reported. On 26 Dec 2020 at 1:58 pm, approximately three hours prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 026L2DA) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 26 Dec 2020, at 5:00 pm, the patient passed out. She also had pain in the injection site and a slight headache. On 27 Dec 2020, at 8:30 am, the patient passed out again. No treatment information was provided. The Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome for the events, passed out twice, pain in the injection site, and slight headache was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 24 year old female patient, who experienced a serious unexpected event of loss of consciousness and non-serious expected event of injection site pain and headache. The event occurred apparently few hours after first dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot # 026L2DA) administration. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

It started out the size of a silver dollar, and over the course of 48 hours the welt, itchiness, and redness grew to the size of a large russet potato (Friday 1/22- Saturday1/23). It was the most red around the injection site, with the most red being about the size of a silver dollar. After 48 hours, it remained itchy, red, and had a welt for the next 24 hours (Sunday 1/24). The next morning (Monday 1/25) redness and swelling were gone but site was still a little itchy. Site was only slightly tender throughout these three days but not painful. No other side effects were noticed i.e. fever, chills, chest pain. Slight dizziness was felt if I hadn't eaten anything.

On January 21 I received my first dose of Moderna vaccine on my left arm. After the vaccine I had a red lump that was hot and a bruise that only lasted 2 days. Everything was fine until the January 28th when I developed a large red lump during the day while at work that was severely itchy and hot. When I got home from work I had a low grade fever. I made an appointment with my primary care for the next day which was Friday the 29th. My doctor told me she believes I had cellulitis. I was given an antibiotic 2x a day for 7 days. She drew a purple circle around the area and told me that if it goes outside the marked area or I feel any new symptoms, to go to the emergency room. Saturday morning on the 30th i woke up to my entire arm red and hot. I felt like I had a huge sunburn. I couldn?t put my sweatshirt on because it was so hot. The emergency room doctor told me I was fine and to keep taking the antibiotics that were given to me yesterday from my primary care doctor. After the emergency room I went to work and started to feel dizzy and nauseous. My hands became sweaty but the rest of my body was cold. I started having a butterfly feeling in my chest. My Apple Watch alerted me that my heart rate was over 100 bpm. That night before bed I had another low grade fever. On Sunday the 31st I noticed the red area was gone but instead it was a dark purple. I felt okay Sunday besides a rapid pulse. Monday February 1st I woke up out of a dead sleep sweating, butterfly feeling in my chest and dizzy. I tried to take my pulse while laying down but it was so fast I couldn?t keep up with it. I put my Apple Watch on which alerted me immediately that my pulse was 152 bpm. I slowly got up but then I passed out falling off of my bed. I couldn?t get any words out because my heart was beating so fast that I couldn?t breathe. I was sweating horribly and had a hard time walking. Had absolutely no strength in my left hand, my arm was purple/red, cold and numb. My arm felt like someone punched me repeatedly and gave me a dead arm. I called my primary doctors office and they were able to get me in that afternoon. All morning my pulse was spiking and then drastically dropping. About an hour and a half before I went to the doctor everything was fine. I was able to talk but still struggled with breathing while talking. The doctor ordered an EKG which came back clear. My pulse and blood pressure was also fine. The doctor told me she believed all of the symptoms I had were from the medication I take at night (doxazosin-to relax my muscles and help with sleep.) She also told me she believed some of it was my mental health issues taking over. She told me the cellulitis looked fine and sent me home. Later that day I felt exhausted and when I woke up from a nap, I had a fever of 100.5. Took Tylenol and it dropped to 99.5 but wouldn?t go any lower. February 2nd I woke up to a large red ring outside of the purple marker, numb finger tips and butterfly feeling in my chest. All day I received alerts that my pulse was falling and spiking. I sent my primary doctor an email and she told me she didn?t think it was cellulitis anymore, maybe a hematoma but she wasn?t sure. Since January 28th I still struggle everyday with the butterfly feeling in my chest, blurry vision, low grade temps, alerts of pulse, dizziness and breathing difficulties. My arm is always hot, my finger tips are numb and sometimes the strength in my hand is gone. The top of my arm is always a dark purple with red blotches and other times my entire arm is red and hot. When my pulse is very fast, I have a hard time talking, remembering what I was going to say and focusing. I?ve had multiple coworkers ask me if I?m okay because I?ll randomly stop talking and stare off and then I?m alerted that my pulse has either spiked or dropped drastically after spiking. My pulse is never consistent. It is always ranging from 57-155bpm. I realized at first I may have what they call ?COVID arm? but my symptoms haven?t gotten any better. No answers have been given to me or a diagnosis. The first diagnosis that they thought was cellulitis. Then it was ?in my head and behavioral.? Then it was a hematoma. Now it?s an ?I don?t know.? I have tried Benadryl for the itching, ice packs for the days that I?m swollen, Tylenol for the fevers and pain but I never have any relief.

The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. No Medical History information was reported. On 17-Apr-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 17-Apr-2021, the patient experienced SYNCOPE (Fainted), ANXIETY (Anxiety high), GENERAL PHYSICAL HEALTH DETERIORATION (general health bad), NAUSEA (Nausea) and PYREXIA (consistent low grade fever (100F to 100.4F)). On 18-Apr-2021, the patient experienced FAECES DISCOLOURED (diarrhea has been all kinds of colors(now orange)/black when she was taking Pepto-Bismol). On 19-Apr-2021, the patient experienced SOMNOLENCE (Cannot keep eyes open at work). On 20-Apr-2021, the patient experienced DIARRHOEA (severe non-stop diarrhea since the day she got her vaccine) and FOREIGN BODY IN GASTROINTESTINAL TRACT (little stomach bug). On 28-Apr-2021, the patient experienced SKIN TIGHTNESS (face feels like it's tightening), DYSMENORRHOEA (painful menstrual period) and PALLOR (Pale as a ghost). At the time of the report, SYNCOPE (Fainted) had resolved, SOMNOLENCE (Cannot keep eyes open at work), SKIN TIGHTNESS (face feels like it's tightening), ANXIETY (Anxiety high), GENERAL PHYSICAL HEALTH DETERIORATION (general health bad), FAECES DISCOLOURED (diarrhea has been all kinds of colors(now orange)/black when she was taking Pepto-Bismol), FOREIGN BODY IN GASTROINTESTINAL TRACT (little stomach bug), DYSMENORRHOEA (painful menstrual period), PALLOR (Pale as a ghost), NAUSEA (Nausea) and PYREXIA (consistent low grade fever (100F to 100.4F)) outcome was unknown and DIARRHOEA (severe non-stop diarrhea since the day she got her vaccine) had not resolved. Not Provided The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. No concomitant medications were reported. Treatment medications include Pepto-Bismol (bismuth subsalicylate) for diarrhea for 1.5 days (unknown dose/frequency). Patient waited out 20 minutes post-vaccination and then went to the bathroom. When she came out of bathroom she fainted, paramedics were summoned. Mother took patient to Emergency Room(ER) 20 April 2021, after taking her first to urgent care (who directed mother to take patient to the ER), ER sent her home saying it was just a little stomach bug, but no one else in the family got this "bug". Patient's last test for Covid-19 was on Monday (26-Apr-2021) and results came back negative on 28-Apr-2021. Company comment: The event of faeces discolored is assessed as unlikely due to mRNA-1273 administration but due ingesting Pepto-Bismol. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the other events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. 25 2021-02-24 vaccination site pain Rapid heartbeat; Shortness of breath; Pain at injection site; Chills; Fatigue; Fever; A spontaneous ... Read more
Close
Rapid heartbeat; Shortness of breath; Pain at injection site; Chills; Fatigue; Fever; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 25 years-old, female patient who experienced rapid heartbeat/MedDRA PT: tachycardia, shortness of breath/MedDRA PT: dyspnoea, pain at injection site/MedDRA PT: vaccination site pain, chills/MedDRA PT: chills, fatigue/MedDRA PT: fatigue, and fever/MedDRA PT: pyrexia. The patient's medical history included anemia and low immune system. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 23 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot # 025A202A) intramuscularly (injection site not provided) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 23 Jan 2021, after receiving vaccination, the patient experienced pain at injection site, chills, fever, fatigue and shortness of breath. On 24 Jan 2021, the patient experienced rapid heartbeat. The patient was hospitalized and during hospitalization, heart rate was noted as 125 bpm which reduced down to 110 bpm. The patient was discharged on 25 Jan 2021. Following hospitalization, patient had ongoing fever and was advised to contact hospital for direction regarding readmission. Treatment included self-administered Tylenol, six times daily. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown. The events chills and shortness of breath were considered resolved on 24 Jan 2021. The events pain at injection site, fatigue, and rapid heartbeat were considered resolved on an unknown date. The event fever was considered not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 25-year-old female who experienced serious expected events of tachycardia and dyspnea along with nonserious expected events of fever, chills, fatigue and vaccination site pain. The events occurred 1 day after the first dose of mRNA-1273. Treatment included Tylenol. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

I went to the toilet feeling nauseous and wretched a few times but did not throw up. I did, however, experience diarrhea that morning and throughout the day. I laid down on the couch and fell in and out of sleep for a few hours. I felt the headache most of the morning, until about 11 AM,. I felt the chills throughout most of the day. I treated my pain with ibuprofen 200mg tablets (3 taken each time, 4-6 hours apart), Pepto-bismol for the nausea and had mostly liquids such as water and juice as well as bread and crackers. I felt much better by around 2 PM, except for the tenderness and swelling in my arm.
